Boil the quails’ eggs in a pan of boiling salted water for 2½ minutes, drain and peel.In a bowl mix the crab with the egg yolk, tarragon, salt and pepper.Wrap this mixture around the quails’ eggs, covering them completely.Prepare three bowls: one with plan flour, another with the egg and milk, and another with breadcrumbsDip the quails’ eggs into first the flour, then the egg wash and finally into the breadcrumbs.Fill a deep-sided pan up to a third with sunflower oil and heat to 160C/325F.  (CAUTION: hot oil can be dangerous. Do not leave unattended.)Place the eggs into the oil and cook for about three minutes, or until golden-brown, then take the eggs out and drain on a plate lined with kitchen paper.